description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint an enthusiastic, self-motivated, experienced secretary to provide comprehensive secretarial support General Surgery. It is essential that applicants possess a high level of audio typing skills, hold Medical Secretarial qualifications and are qualified to a minimum of RSA Stage 2 (or equivalent). The successful applicant will be able to work on their own initiative and be able to work as part of a team. The post holder will be able to work within time constraints and be able to meet deadlines whilst being able to demonstrate good organisational skills and the ability to maintain good and reliable records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leana Hayes&lt;br /&gt;Leana.Hayes@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;03000 858333&lt;/p&gt;
